          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-05-30 15:35:32" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>any light-producing object in the sky, such as the sun, moon, and other planets and stars</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>light</Gloss>
                <Gloss>luminary</Gloss>
                <Gloss>star</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Though φωστήρ[a] may refer to any light-producing object, it is used especially of the heavenly bodies and more specifically of stars, as in {S:05000201500036}, the one NT context in which φωστήρ[a] occurs. A focal component of this meaning is the light-giving characteristic.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
